-- Russia's VTB takes 8 bln rbls hit from Ukraine crisis in Q2
-- By Oksana Kobzeva and Alexander Winning
-- Thu Aug 21, 2014 04:34AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Aug 21 (Reuters) - VTB <VTBR.MM>, Russia's second biggest bank, estimates the negative effect from the Ukraine crisis at 8 billion roubles ($220  million) in the second quarter of 2014, the bank's senior vice-president Dmitry Pyanov told a conference call.

